This paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning for decision-making in autonomous driving, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a simulated object list similar to that of radar or lidar sensors, which suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the use of neural networks for decision-making indicates a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a semantic scene description, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the agent's ability to adhere to traffic rules and drive safely, which suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY).
